-- Deutsche Telekom, Vivendi Agree to Drop PTC Claims, Polish Ministry Says
-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 2010-12-15T07:58:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/deutsche-telekom-vivendi-agree-to-drop-ptc-claims-polish-ministry-says.html
Deutsche Telekom AG, Vivendi SA and
Warsaw-based Elektrim SA have reached a preliminary agreement to
resolve their dispute over control of Polish mobile-phone
operator Polska Telefonia Cyfrowa Sp. z o.o., the Polish
Treasury Ministry said today in a statement on its website.  The Ministry said that the three sides had agreed to drop
legal claims against each other over a 48 percent stake in the
operator. As part of the deal, Elektrim will pay the Treasury
389.9 million zloty, the statement said, adding that legal
conditions need to be met for the agreement to be finalized.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
